@NODE "intro.hlp"
@TITLE "Introduction"
@PREV "licen.hlp"
@NEXT "001"

               Introduction - Installation - Quickstart
@{U}@{FG shine}                                                                             @{UU}@{FG text}

 NOTE:

 Introduction
 ------------

   Are you sometimes unable to find the correct graphics for a specific problem ?
   Do you sometimes lose the details of how your graphics are named and saved ?
   Wouldn't it be convenient to administrate, display, print, scan, process,
   convert and export these graphics with only one single application ?
   Do you often wish to you could convert your graphics archives from one
   format into the other automatically ?

   With the PictureManager professional you have a program which
   makes graphics administration as easy as possible. Additionally it
   offers powerful functions for graphics conversion, image processing.

  Fields of PMPro usage
  ---------------------

   PMPro is a visual database for bitmapped graphics of different kinds
   as well as IFF animation's. More than ever, in the age of CD-ROM 
   and other large storage media, the user is confronted with large numbers
   of graphics. Also many programs supply large picture and clipart libraries
   which can be used for own purposes.
   To find the right graphic is most often nearly impossible, since
   the naming of the graphics usually does not tell a great deal about it!
   With PMPro you can comfortably manage your graphics, which are
   displayed as miniature pictures (thumbnails) on the screen.
   Using simple mouseclicks, you can display, print and even export these
   to programs like DPaint IV, PPaint and AdPro. An integrated image
   processing module and the possibility to convert graphics into
   other formats completes the package and makes PMPro a universal and
   irreplaceable graphics tool. PMPro offers many time saving features that
   are unique in one single package.


  Important Information
  ---------------------

    A great deal of care was taken during the creation of this manual and 
    software. Nevertheless programming faults never can completely be excluded.
    Because of this, we cannot guarantee a 100% error-free working of
    the program on your computer system. The reasons for this are
    mainly the many different hardware configurations, which may not
    all be covered by testing efforts. Often the problem is not
    actually caused by Picture Manager but by errors of third party
    software or hardware.

  System Requirements
  -------------------

   For working with the Picture Manager professional
   your Amiga needs to fulfil the following requirements:

     * OS 2.1 or greater

     * at least 3 MB FAST RAM

     * Hard disk

    Recommended : At least 4-8 MB FAST RAM and an 68020 (or faster).

   If your Amiga conforms to this requirements you may directly
   install the program.

  Installation
  ------------

   Installation of the PMPro is quite easy and performed automatically
   when started by a double click onto the Install_HD icon on the
   program diskette. Just boot your Amiga as usual, then insert the
   disk and start the script. A requester appears, and the drive or
   drawer for installation of PMPro has to be selected. A directory 
   "PicManager" will be created within the selceted destination, in which
   the program will reside. After completion of the installation you will 
   have to reboot the machine to be able to work with PMPro.

   If you get an error during installation (can not compile script) please
   copy the "installer" from Disk 1 to your C:-Directory on your harddisk!

  Getting Started
  ---------------

   Now, double click on the program icon of PMPro within the
   drawer "PicManager" and select a screenmode within the
   requester that will appear.
   You should now take the time to correctly configure the program.
   Via "PROGRAM/DISPLAY/SETTINGS" you should specify the display driver
   you wish to use (if you have any troubles with this please see the corresponding
   chapter). To set up any connected CD-ROMs drive you have to use
   "PROGRAM/SETTINGS/PHOTO CD". Also other important configurations
   can be done in the PROGRAM/Settings-menu with its submenus and
   in the PROGRAM-PMPRO ENVIROMENT menu.

   These are the most important settings to enable you to quickly get started.
   Configuration of popup menus, ARexx pulldowns or quick menus may be
   performed later after you get some experience using the PMPro.

   Now to get into the more interesting part!
   The program already includes two sample catalogues with some graphics
   and clipart from the public domain, so that you may immediately
   test some of the functions of the program.
   Select "Load Catalogue" to load one of the two demo catalogues.
   You may now simply perform a "learning by doing" process and test some
   of the functions. For example, activate the picture specific context
   (display graphics, image processing, etc.) by clicking once on a thumbnail 
   on the screen. To begin with cataloguing of the example graphics, you should
   follow these steps:

      * Create a new catalogue via "Catalog/New"

      * Scan the complete drawer for graphics via "Expand/Whole Directory" 

      * Should graphics be found, a window will list all of them

      * Select "expand". A status window will inform you of
        the current progress of cataloguing.

      * After a short time you will see the graphics in the form of
        miniaturised thumbnails on the screen

   You may now examine the Tools directory of PMPro, where you
   can find various useful programs for image processing, conversion
   and so on. Although being mostly easy and self-explanatory you should
   carefully read the rest of this manual to be able to use all of the functions
   and configuration features fully!

   And now: Enjoy using Picture Manager Professional!

  Working With Catalogues
  -----------------------

   A catalogue is the central element within PMPro. It represents
   an individual user collection of thumbnails of different graphics
   and animation's. The number of catalogues is not limited, but a single
   catalogue is only designed to hold a number of up to 999 graphics.
   This is perhaps just a theoretical limit, since you may create
   an unlimited number of catalogues, anyway.

   Note: PMPro is an excellent tool for sorting and administrating your
         large archives of graphics and clipart, but it is only as
         efficient as you allow it to be for hierarchical orders.
         So you should make your catalogues context related and not
         too large - to prevent you from turning an undocumented
         picture chaos into a visually supported picture chaos!




  Product Overview
  ----------------

   PMPro includes a number of possibilities for visually
   administrating, processing, scanning, printing
   and converting graphics.

   Following is a list of the most important features:


      * PPC support (ppc.library)

      * Searches whole directories, and also recursively searches
        entire harddrives, removeable media, CD-ROMS etc.
        for bitmapped graphics and IFF animations.

      * Recognizes over 40 graphics file formats (IFF, GIF, JPEG, TIFF, MAC-
        Pict, BMP, PCX, TARGA, PCD, IFF-DEEP, SGI, SunRaster, YUVN and many             more) as well as IFF animations (OPT5, OPT7 and Opt8). Also,
        postscript is supported via the PD software Ghostscript.

      * Saver modules for ca. 15 graphics file formats. Automated
        conversion and processing of graphics to any graphics file format.

      * Direct scanner support (ScanQuix3 device)

      * Reading of contact sheet files of Kodak Photo CD.

      * Integrated WebWizard for automated generation of HTML pages.

      * Up to 100 thumbnails displayable per screen page, depending
        on the selected screenmode. Display of these thumbnails is possible
        in three different sizes, as well in greyscales as colours. Coloured
        display requires the AGA chipset or an appropriate graphic card.

      * Supports resolutions up to 1280x1024 pixels with graphic cards.

      * High thumbnail quality through dithering as well as sharpness
        and contrast adjustment.

      * Automated copying and reorganisation of whole image databases.

      * Direct support for LHA and LZX archives.

      * Display modules for AGA, ECS, Retina, PicassoII, EGS, Merlin,
        CyberGraphics and Picasso96.

      * It is also possible to display all graphics in a separate window
        on PMPro's main screen.

      * Integration of external image viewers for each graphics file format
        is individually configurable.

      * Freely selectable screenmode via viewmode requester.

      * Freely configurable user interface and mouse button functionality.

      * Playing of IFF animations (Opt5, Opt7 and Opt8). When memory
        is low these can also be played directly from hard disk.

      * Direct exporting of graphics to any other programs, like for example
        DPaint, PPaint, ADPro, ImageFX etc.

      * Diverse catalogue printing functions, including table format and
        also graphically with freely selectable layout.

      * Ability to directly print any graphic formats with direct support
        of TurboPrint. The size of the printing and selectable image sections
        can be specified by the user.

      * Integrated 24 bit image processing application (incl. preview)
        with functions like:

             - Brightness and contrast adjustment
             - Gamma correction
             - Modification of red, green and blue components
             - Colour reduction incl. dithering
             - Rotating and scaling
             - Mirroring
             - Convolution filters
             - Sharpness correction
             - Edge detection
             - Blur filter
             - Emboss filter
             - Mosaic and antique effects
             - Conversion of graphic file formats
             - and many more

      * Many functions for sorting and searching

      * System-conforming interface and requesters.

      * Some areas have freely configurable menus.

      * Freely configurable tool bars (quick menus).

      * Online-help

        and many, many more features............


  Hardware requirements
  ---------------------

       Amiga with a minimum of 4Mb RAM, OS 2.1 or greater and a hard disk.

       Recommended:  When using with 24-bit graphics 8Mb or more FAST RAM is    
                     required.



                      

  Service
  -------

   Users of PMPro should contact Blittersoft for product news, as PMPro is
   under continuous development.  


       
@ENDNODE
@NODE "new.hlp"
@TITLE "New features in version 5"
@PREV "intro.hlp"

The new features of version 5 in a quick overview:

* Integrated WebWizard:

  This powerful tool allows automated creation of HTML pages from a  
  PictureManager catalogue. So now you can view PMPro catalogues
  with any web browser, on any platform (MAC, Unix, Win95, WinNT ...).

* Automated Image Processing:

  When converting image collections, you can now additionally define up to 5  
  image processing operators that will be automatically applied.

* Conversion of Catalogues:

  PMPro5 now includes a tool to convert catalogues to different thumbnail
  sizes or colour depths. This way, for example,a colour catalogue with 144x112
  pixels can be changed into a greyscaled catalogue with 120x96 pixel size.

* GFX-Pages:

  The function Extras/IFF-Pages has been extended with the function Extras/GFX- 
  Pages. Apart from many choices for layout settings, you can now also freely  
  Select the graphics file format in which the overview pages will be saved.

* Catalogue printing:

  When printing catalogues there are now many choices for page layout, such as 
  freely selectable row and column numbers and various text options with freely  
  definable bottom lines.

* Preview for Image Processing:

  The Image Processing functionality of PMPro now allows a simple preview
  before applying the corresponding image processing operator.

* Increased speed and more improvements / Extended Load, Save and Image  
  Processing Modules

* New GFX formats: FAXX, RGB8, DXF, AMF, IFF-DR2D

* ASSIGN keywords automatic to all marked / searched entries

* Saving of window positions

* PowerPC Support:

  Calculation-intensive loader and image processing routines have been redone
  as optimised PowerPC code. PPC boards using the PowerUp standard are  
  automatically recognised.


@ENDNODE
